TO: WILLIAM MCGUIRE

TLS (XEROX), 1 p.

Montreux, Switzerland





June 14, 1963

Dear Mr. McGuire,

I am worried by the reference to "aspersions" in your letter of June 10. I do not have my text here but whatever "aspersions" I cast on the Deutsch-Elton-Radin-Spalding versions, they should not be diluted. Please, send me my text of the "aspersions". As far as I remember that passage, it was a ver